<TITLE> RAB arrest 4 suspected robbers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) arrested 4 armed men suspecting them to be robbers at Muradpur in Chittagong on Thursday. The arrested are Sirajul Islam, 30, Abu Jaker, 28, Md Nasir, 35, and Md Rafieuqe, 35. Staff officer of RAB-7 assistant police superintendent Saidul Islam told bdnews24.com that they had arrested the men from Jalal Plaza of Muradpur at around 2pm when they were about to rob a local bank. RAB seized two pipe guns, a machete and a large chopper from them. Islam said that they had also seized the auto rickshaw that they used. Legal steps will be taken against them, the police officer said. 
